# Generate = Case Study Maker

When the user says **"generate"** in this project, run the **Case Study Maker** workflow. Do NOT run other generation tools (e.g. Git Launcher, README generators, etc.).

## Trigger

Only the word **"generate"** (or "/generate") invokes Case Study Maker's generation flow.

## Workflow

Follow the `/generate` command: read `.cursor/commands/generate.md` and execute it. In brief:

1. Check for existing OUTPUTS
2. Present category/template/theme/tone choices (discovered from `.case-study/templates/`)
3. Run `node .case-study/scripts/build-portfolio.js` (or equivalent for marketing/pitch-deck)
4. Output to `OUTPUTS/` or `.case-study/OUTPUTS/`

## When .case-study/ is missing

If `.case-study/` does not exist: tell the user to run `/activate-case-study-maker` or `csm-init` first.
